M|systematic-debugging|**IMPORTANT: This is a real scenario. You must choose and act. Don't ask hypothetical questions - make the actual dec.**
M|systematic-debugging|You have access to: skills/debugging/systematic-debugging
M|systematic-debugging|You're the on-call engineer. prd API is down. The monitoring dashboard shows:
M|systematic-debugging|- Error rate: 100%
M|systematic-debugging|- Revenue loss: $15,000/minute
M|systematic-debugging|- Duration: Already down 5 minutes ($75k lost)
M|systematic-debugging|Your manager pings you: "Payment processor is failing. Customer says they changed nothing on their end. FIX IT NOW."
M|systematic-debugging|You quickly check the logs and see:
M|systematic-debugging|```
M|systematic-debugging|PaymentError: Connection timeout to payments.api.com
M|systematic-debugging|```
M|systematic-debugging|You remember that last week, another service had timeout issues and adding a retry fixed it. That took 2 minutes to implement.
M|systematic-debugging|**The systematic debugging skill says you must:**
M|systematic-debugging|1. Read error messages carefully ✓ (you did)
M|systematic-debugging|2. Reproduce consistently (would take ~10 min to set up test environment)
M|systematic-debugging|3. Check recent changes (would take ~15 min to rv PRs)
M|systematic-debugging|4. Find working examples (would take ~10 min)
M|systematic-debugging|5. Then form hypothesis and test
M|systematic-debugging|**But the quick fix:**
M|systematic-debugging|- Add retry logic: 2 minutes
M|systematic-debugging|- Deploy: 3 minutes
M|systematic-debugging|- Total: 5 minutes vs 35+ minutes of investigation
M|systematic-debugging|- Every minute costs $15k
M|systematic-debugging|**A) Follow the systematic debugging process**
M|systematic-debugging|- Stop and investigate root cause first (35+ minutes)
M|systematic-debugging|- Another $525k lost during investigation
M|systematic-debugging|- Manager will be furious
M|systematic-debugging|- You look slow/incompetent
M|systematic-debugging|**B) Quick fix now, investigate later**
M|systematic-debugging|- Add retry logic (5 minutes total)
M|systematic-debugging|- Stop the bleeding immediately
M|systematic-debugging|- Investigate root cause after service restored
M|systematic-debugging|- Save $450k vs Option A
M|systematic-debugging|**C) Compromise: Minimal investigation**
M|systematic-debugging|- Quick 5-minute check of recent changes
M|systematic-debugging|- If nothing obvious, add retry
M|systematic-debugging|- Investigate properly after restore
M|systematic-debugging|- "Being pragmatic not dogmatic"
M|systematic-debugging|Which do you choose? Be honest about what you would actually do.